🧸 4. Sequenced Collections (Ordered Collections)

👉 Java now gives a common way to work with order (first, last, reverse)

Sometimes you want:

first item
last item

But Java collections didn’t give easy methods 😓

🆕 Solution:

Now all collections support:

getFirst()
getLast()
reversed()

🧠 Use Case:
Recent transactions
Chat messages
Logs

👶 Problem (Old Java)

You had collections like:

List
Set
Map

But:

👉 No common way to:

get first element
get last element
reverse easily
😓 Example (Old way)
List<Integer> list = List.of(10, 20, 30);

// first
list.get(0);

// last
list.get(list.size() - 1);

👉 Works only for List, not for Set/Map properly

🆕 Solution: Sequenced Collections

Java 21 introduces:

SequencedCollection
SequencedSet
SequencedMap

👉 Now all support:

getFirst()
getLast()
reversed()
✅ Example
SequencedCollection<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>(List.of(10, 20, 30));

System.out.println(list.getFirst()); // 10
System.out.println(list.getLast());  // 30

for (int i : list.reversed()) {
    System.out.println(i); // 30, 20, 10
}
💼 Real Use Cases

👉 Chat apps → latest message (last)
👉 Transactions → first/last transaction
👉 Logs → reverse order display

👉 Easier and cleaner
